race.description: Spelling At Coolmore Mt White F&M (Bm78) Handicap
race.comment: BESIDE THE OCEAN (11) away only fairly and never looked comfortable on the tight Wyong track before making ground in the straight when fourth over 1100m. Near her top now and desperate for this trip and further third-up. Winning rider goes back on and she can get the job done. CANDLEWICK (3) resumed for the Joe Pride yard with an eye catching third over 1100m at this track. Will come on strongly for this and expected to race a touch closer. Genuine top-three player. HEAT MISSILE (10) slashing effort on resumption from back in the field when sixth over 1100m at Wyong. Proven second-up performer who will need a touch of luck again from the draw. Capable of featuring. DIDDLE DUMPLING (4) underrated mare who returns from a lengthy break. Good fresh performer fitted with the two sound trials over 900m. Should get the right conditions to figure prominently. USEAPIN (1) had mixed luck in two runs back and no surprise to see J Mac get the best out of her from the inside gate.
